Material.Fire-rated walls: Required for garages at the lot line

Usage.Uncovered spaces: Beyond required front-yard and first 10' of street-side yard

Specs.Uniform Building Code: Compliance required for fire-rated walls & roof materials

Mandatory: Garages at the lot line must comply with UBC requirements
Carports with open sides must be at least 3' from any lot line
Conditional logic: On lots less than 95' deep, garages/carports may be located in rear or interior side yards if placed in rear half of the lot

Exceptions.Explicit deviations: Garages and carports that take advantage of setback exception are subject to stricter daylight plane
Exceptions.Alternatives: 1-car garage could be substituted for a 2-car garage

Relationships.Cross-references: See Figs 25–26 p. 32 for daylight plane
Relationships.Logical dependencies: Garages/carports location depends on lot depth and setback requirements
